🧠 CATEGORIES — RECORD VIEW + EXECUTION LAYER SPEC
Second Fully Governed Table Under the Record View Engine
🔷 0. PURPOSE

Categories is the second system entity to be fully governed by:

* Record View Engine (UI + Controller)
* Execution Layer (Transport → Application → Domain → Data → Infra)

UOM established the seed pattern. Categories follows it exactly — with one
meaningful increase in complexity: a richer form (5 UOM unit selectors) and
a delete rule that must be expanded to a structured link state object.

This spec documents what needs to move, what is already correct, and where
the current implementation diverges from the canonical execution standard.

---

🔷 1. ENTITY DEFINITION

📦 Category

Represents a flooring product category. Categories govern how products are
measured and grouped across the system.

Fields:
* id
* name (unique)
* sendUnitId (FK → FlooringUnitOfMeasure)
* stockUnitId (FK → FlooringUnitOfMeasure)
* coverageAvailableUnitId (FK → FlooringUnitOfMeasure)
* itemCoverageUnitId (FK → FlooringUnitOfMeasure)
* serviceUnitId (FK → FlooringUnitOfMeasure)
* createdAt
* updatedAt

---

🔗 Relationships

* A Category has 5 UOM unit fields (send, stock, coverageAvailable, itemCoverage, service)
  — these are FKs from Category TO UnitOfMeasure. Deleting a UOM is blocked if
    it is linked to a Category (handled by the UOM spec, not here).
* A Category can be linked to Products (FlooringProduct[])
* A Category CANNOT be deleted if any products reference it



---

🔴 CRITICAL BUSINESS RULE

❗ A Category CANNOT be deleted if it is referenced by any Product record.

Ownership of this Rule:
👉 Domain Layer (source of truth)

Current gap:
The existing `isCategoryDeleteBlocked(productCount: number)` takes a raw number.
This must be refactored to accept a `CategoryDeleteLinkState` struct — consistent
with the pattern established by UOM, Contacts, and Services in packages/domain.

Correct target:
  isCategoryDeleteBlocked({ productLinks }: CategoryDeleteLinkState): boolean
  getCategoryDeleteBlockedMessage(state: CategoryDeleteLinkState): string

Enforcement also appears at:
* Application (final guard before mutation, inside transaction)
* Transport (early rejection via assertExpectedUpdatedAt + enforceMutationReceipt)
* Data (FK constraints as a last-resort defensive layer)

