🔷 6. CLIENT-SIDE TRANSPORT FIX (mutations.ts)

Current gap in data/mutations.ts:

  export async function deleteCategoryRequest(id: string) {
    return requestJson<{ success: boolean }>(`/api/flooring/categories/${id}`, {
      method: "DELETE",
    })
  }

❌ Sends no body — the DELETE route requires expectedUpdatedAt via parseMutationEnvelope.
The record panel controller works correctly because it calls requestJson inline with
withMutationMeta. But the mutations.ts exported function is broken for any caller
that uses it directly.

Target fix:

  export async function deleteCategoryRequest(id: string, updatedAt: string) {
    return requestJson<{ ok: true }>(`/api/flooring/categories/${id}`, {
      method: "DELETE",
      headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
      body: JSON.stringify(withMutationMeta({}, updatedAt)),
    })
  }

This aligns with the pattern established by deleteUnitOfMeasure in unit-of-measures/data/mutations.ts.

