🔷 7. END-TO-END FLOWS

💾 Save (Update Primary Section)

User edits name or any unit selector
    ↓
Controller detects dirty state
    ↓
User clicks Save
    ↓
Controller → Transport (PATCH /api/flooring/categories/:id/primary/section)
    ↓
Transport: applyRoutePolicy (auth + rate limit) + parseMutationEnvelope
    + assertExpectedUpdatedAt + enforceMutationReceipt
    ↓
Application.updateCategoryUseCase(id, input) — orchestrates:
    ↓
  [1] Application asks Domain → normalizeCategoryNameForUniqueness (pure)
    ↓
  [2] Application asks Data → categoryNameExists (fetch the fact)
    ↓
  [3] Application asks Domain → assertCategoryNameAvailable (evaluate the rule)
    ↓
  [4] Application asks Data → updateCategoryRecord (execute the mutation)
    ↓
  [5] Application asks Data → getCategoryById (fetch authoritative snapshot)
    ↓
Transport returns { category: snapshot }
    ↓
Controller replaces state with snapshot
    ↓
dirty = false, UI updates

🗑️ Delete

User clicks Delete
    ↓
UI: confirmation dialog
    ↓
Controller → Transport (DELETE /api/flooring/categories/:id)
    body: withMutationMeta({}, record.updatedAt)
    ↓
Transport: applyRoutePolicy + parseMutationEnvelope
    + assertExpectedUpdatedAt + enforceMutationReceipt
    ↓
Application.deleteCategoryUseCase(id) — orchestrates:
    ↓
  [1] Application asks Data → getCategoryDeleteState(id)
         ↳ returns { productLinks: number } or null
    ↓
  [2] if null → throw CategoryExecutionError({ code: "CATEGORY_NOT_FOUND", status: 404 })
    ↓
  [3] Application asks Domain → isCategoryDeleteBlocked(deleteState)
         ↳ Domain is the authority — evaluates the rule, no DB access
    ↓
  ❌ Domain blocks → Application throws CategoryExecutionError({ code: "CATEGORY_IN_USE", status: 409 })
         ↓
      Transport normalizes → routeError returns { error: { code, message } }
         ↓
      Controller surfaces error to UI
         ↓
      UI displays: "This category is linked to products and cannot be deleted"
    ↓
  ✅ Domain approves → Application asks Data → deleteCategoryRecord(id)
    ↓
Transport returns { ok: true }
    ↓
Controller navigates away or refreshes list

