🔷 8. ERROR HANDLING

Domain Error Shape:
{
  code: "CATEGORY_IN_USE",
  message: "This category is linked to products and cannot be deleted",
  status: 409,
}

{
  code: "CATEGORY_NAME_CONFLICT",
  message: "Category name must be unique",
  status: 409,
  field: "name",
}

{
  code: "CATEGORY_NOT_FOUND",
  message: "Category not found",
  status: 404,
}

Error Flow:
Domain throws → Application classifies → Transport normalizes → Controller receives → UI displays

UI Behavior:
* Show error in section (scoped to the action, not the whole page)
* Error dismisses on next user action
* Delete button remains active — blocked state is only surfaced after the attempt
  (consistent with UOM behavior — we do not pre-query link counts on panel open)

