🔷 11. HOW CATEGORIES RELATES TO UOM (THE SEED PATTERN)

Categories follows the UOM pattern exactly with two differences:

1. Richer form: 5 unit selector fields vs. 1 name field
   — Same execution path, more payload fields. No structural difference.

2. Delete rule input: CategoryDeleteLinkState vs. UnitOfMeasureDeleteLinkState
   — UOM checks categoryLinks + serviceLinks (two link types)
   — Category checks productLinks (one link type — schema only has products)
   — Both use the same struct-based domain rule pattern

Everything else is structurally identical:
* Same error class shape (ExecutionError with code, message, status)
* Same route policy pattern (applyRoutePolicy)
* Same mutation envelope pattern (withMutationMeta)
* Same controller hook (useSingleSectionRecordController)
* Same packages split (domain / db / execution)

